			<div class="content" id="post-content-2824585">
									

<p>Hello! I'm LilyFlower, Operational Staff here on the wiki, and this thread is a place for you, the users, to ask staff questions. What about? Most things! See below for more details.</p>
<p><span style="font-size:larger;">A few rules:</span></p>
<ul>
<li>Don't be rude- follow the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/site-rules">site and forum rules</a> at all times.</li>
<li>Don't spam the thread with multiple questions in quick succession, or many silly questions. If you have multiple questions, put them all in one post.</li>
<li>Joke questions are okay, but we also want serious ones about what it's like to be staff, and the site.</li>
<li>Try not to post questions that have already been asked.</li>
<li>This isn't the place for questions about basic site help, <strong>or for drafts and ideas help</strong>. Please put these in the respective boards. Questions about the writing process of staff are allowed, though!</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-size:larger;">Useful links:</span></p>
<ul>
<li>The <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/meet-the-staff">staff list and bios</a>!</li>
<li>The previous <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-702417/senior-staff:faq-discussion">Ask Staff thread</a>. Be aware this is a few years old and is a bit out of date, and no longer active. You can ask questions already answered here- the answer may have changed!</li>
<li>The <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/faq">FAQ</a>, just in case!</li>
</ul>
<p>Other than that, ask us anything! We encourage questions about staff and the staff processes on the site. Good ideas for questions could include queries about the site, the staff structure, future or present projects, writing processes, or just about staff themselves.</p>
<p><strong>All Operational Staff members or above are permitted to reply to questions here, as well as ask them.</strong></p>
<p>ETA 08/11/17: Moved from General to Proposals/Policy.</p>

