			<div class="content" id="post-content-2824636">
									

<p>I'm on Internet Outreach, and I help run both of our official tumblr blogs (did you know we have two?). It's pretty fun, but still work. There's obviously all the normal staff duties, too- deletion votes, bad crit, spam- which we all deal with. That's less fun but needs to be done.</p>
<p>Like ProcyonLotor said, staff aren't (usually) on a strict time schedule, and are able to plan out exactly what and when we do things. We still follow the orders and requests of the admins/mods/team captains, of course. We don't get paid, or anything like that, but the work is rewarding and someone has to do it. It's nice being able to help look after something you care about.</p>
<p>I'm also a half-operator in <a href="http://scp.bz/chat">#site19</a>, our IRC room! I help run it, handling any issues that crop up, and making sure it all goes smoothly. If you haven't already, I'd recommend checking it out.</p>

