<blockquote>
<p>What is the process, life, and workload of staff? Is this a cool kids club? Do you guys get paid?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Workload depends on the staff member. I don't know how cool people think we are, but I definitely tend to feel more like I'm on a cleanup/maintenance crew than a cool kids club.</p>
<p>No one here gets paid for staff work.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>So, staff, describe WHAT YOU DO on a daily basis for this totally-not-for-money, volunteer thing you do.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Standard things for a Zyn:</p>
<ul>
<li>Answer PMs. Dear god. I get so many PMs.</li>
<li>Draft review. Ideas review. Reviews in PMs.</li>
<li>Respond to user complaints in chat and wikidot PMs.</li>
<li>Check staff records for any recent problem users.</li>
<li>Watch Recent Posts like a hawk.</li>
<li>Observe forums for problematic feedback. Comment on problematic feedback should it occur.</li>
<li>Delegate review tasks to other staff members as group time and energy permit.</li>
<li>Occasionally run deletions/deletion votes.</li>
<li><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">zyn must be swift as a coursing river with all the force of a great typhoon with all the strength of a raging fire mysterious as the dark side of the moon</span></li>
</ul>

