														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2824946">
									

<p>I'm the current captain of the Wikiwalk team, a member of Site Crit, and very recently was made a moderator. On any given day my workload for the site looks kind of like this:</p>
<ul>
<li>Answer any PMs sent my way. I don't get as many as the admins, but a few people do request draft feedback from me via Wikidot PM or ask Wikiwalk questions</li>
<li>Run deletion votes/deletions (whether this is a massive sweep or a few deletions here or there depends on my time limits, cause real life.)</li>
<li>Read SCP articles slated for potential Wikiwalk Crosslinks.</li>
<li>Propose Wikiwalk Crosslinks to articles (I usually do about two to five a day depending on a variety of factors)</li>
<li>Add Wikiwalk Crosslinks to articles whose timers have expired/permission given by the author.</li>
<li>Hang out in IRC where I respond to Wikiwalk Team questions as they arrive and provide draft crit as it is asked of me.</li>
</ul>
<p>Everything else is kind of done on an as needed basis for me. The only time schedules I'm restricted too on these are usually the ones I make for myself, which is really nice.</p>
<p>Hope you found all that illuminating.</p>

