				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jacob-conwell" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1372582); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1372582&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204957" alt="Jacob Conwell" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1372582)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jacob-conwell" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1372582); return false;" >Jacob Conwell</a></span> <span class="odate time_1495082315 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">18 May 2017 04:38</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2824954">
									

<p>For me, its made me look at the site more in terms as a whole than on an individual basis.</p>
<p>As just a member of the community, your focus may be on your own work and creating your own niche within the shared universe. Aside from the site rules and what friends you make among the community you aren't really that beholden to anyone.</p>
<p>When you get bumped up to staff, however, you become beholden to the community, and your focus can't be so introspective. As part of the team at the steering wheel its your job to help ensure the site as a whole remains a fun and inviting place to be where people can create their own niches withing the SCP universe.</p>
<p>It really makes you take a step from your little corner of the sandbox and start considering the sandbox as a whole.</p>
<p>Hope that provided some insight.</p>

							</div>

								
					
